ece.code.documentation: Generic decription of the code-specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

ece.code.description.documentation: Short description of the software (type, purpose)

ece.code.library.documentation: List of external libraries used by the code that has produced this IDS

ece.code.library[:].description.documentation: Short description of the software (type, purpose)

ece.code.library[:].parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

ece.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

ece.code.parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

ece.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

ece.ids_properties.comment.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

ece.ids_properties.creation_date.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

ece.ids_properties.homogeneous_time.documentation: This node must be filled (with 0, 1, or 2) for the IDS to be valid. If 1, the time of this IDS is homogeneous, i.e. the time values for this IDS are stored in the time node just below the root of this IDS. If 0, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. In the case only constant or static nodes are filled within the IDS, homogeneous_time must be set to 2

ece.ids_properties.occurrence.description: occurrence number [NOTE: this field only exists in OMAS and is not part of the ITER PDM]

ece.ids_properties.plugins.documentation: Information about the plugins used to write/read this IDS. This structure is filled automatically by the Access Layer at GET/PUT time, no need to fill it via a user program.

ece.ids_properties.plugins.infrastructur.documentation: Plugin infrastructure used to GET the data
Short description of the software (type, purpose)
Plugin infrastructure used to PUT the data
Short description of the software (type, purpose)

ece.ids_properties.plugins.node.documentation: Set of IDS nodes for which a plugin has been applied

ece.ids_properties.plugins.node[:].get_o.documentation: Plugins actually used to read back a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, listed in reverse order of application). This information is filled by the plugin infrastructure during the GET operation.
Short description of the software (type, purpose)
List of the code specific parameters in XML format

ece.ids_properties.plugins.node[:].path.documentation: Path of the node within the IDS, following the syntax given in the link below. If empty, means the plugin applies to the whole IDS.

ece.ids_properties.plugins.node[:].put_o.documentation: Plugins used to PUT a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, if so they are listed by order of application)
Short description of the software (type, purpose)
List of the code specific parameters in XML format

ece.ids_properties.plugins.node[:].readb.documentation: Plugins to be used to read back a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, listed in reverse order of application)
Short description of the software (type, purpose)
List of the code specific parameters in XML format

ece.ids_properties.provenance.node.documentation: Set of IDS nodes for which the provenance is given. The provenance information applies to the whole structure below the IDS node. For documenting provenance information for the whole IDS, set the size of this array of structure to 1 and leave the child "path" node empty

ece.ids_properties.provenance.node[:].pa.documentation: Path of the node within the IDS, following the syntax given in the link below. If empty, means the provenance information applies to the whole IDS.

ece.ids_properties.provenance.node[:].so.documentation: List of sources used to import or calculate this node, identified as explained below. In case the node is the result of of a calculation / data processing, the source is an input to the process described in the "code" structure at the root of the IDS. The source can be an IDS (identified by a URI or a persitent identifier, see syntax in the link below) or non-IDS data imported directly from an non-IMAS database (identified by the command used to import the source, or the persistent identifier of the data source). Often data are obtained by a chain of processes, however only the last process input are recorded here. The full chain of provenance has then to be reconstructed recursively from the provenance information contained in the data sources.

ece.ids_properties.provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

ece.ids_properties.source.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...). Superseeded by the new provenance structure.

ece.ids_properties.version_put.documentation: Version of the access layer package used to PUT this IDS

ece.ids_properties.version_put.access_la.documentation: Version of Access Layer used to PUT this IDS
Programming language of the Access Layer high level API used to PUT this IDS

ece.ids_properties.version_put.data_dict.documentation: Version of Data Dictionary used to PUT this IDS

ece.latency.documentation: Upper bound of the delay between physical information received by the detector and data available on the real-time (RT) network.

ece.latency_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "latency"

ece.line_of_sight.documentation: Description of the line of sight of the diagnostic (valid for all channels), defined by two points. By convention, the first point is the closest to the diagnostic

ece.line_of_sight.first_point.phi.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

ece.line_of_sight.first_point.phi_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "phi"

ece.line_of_sight.first_point.r_error_in.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "r"

ece.line_of_sight.first_point.z_error_in.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"

ece.line_of_sight.second_point.phi.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

ece.line_of_sight.second_point.phi_error.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "phi"

ece.line_of_sight.second_point.r_error_i.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "r"

ece.line_of_sight.second_point.z_error_i.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"

ece.polarizer.documentation: Set of polarizers placed in front of the diagnostic (if any). Polarizers are assumed to be orthogonal to the line of sight, so that the x3 unit vector is aligned with the line of sight

ece.polarizer[:].centre.documentation: If geometry_type=2, coordinates of the centre of the circle. If geometry_type=1 or 3, coordinates of the origin of the local coordinate system (X1,X2,X3) describing the plane polarizer. This origin is located within the polarizer area. Note that there is some flexibility here and the data provider should choose the most convenient coordinate system for the object, respecting the definitions of (X1,X2,X3) indicated below.

ece.polarizer[:].centre.phi.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

ece.polarizer[:].centre.phi_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "phi"

ece.polarizer[:].centre.r_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "r"

ece.polarizer[:].centre.z_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"

ece.polarizer[:].polarization_angle.documentation: Alignment angle of the polarizer in the (x1,x2) plane. Electric fields parallel to the polarizer angle will be reflected. The angle is defined with respect to the x1 unit vector, positive in the counter-clockwise direction when looking towards the plasma

ece.polarizer[:].polarization_angle_erro.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "polarization_angle"

ece.polarizer[:].radius.documentation: Radius of the circle, used only if geometry_type = 2

ece.polarizer[:].radius_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "radius"

ece.polarizer[:].x1_unit_vector.documentation: Components of the X1 direction unit vector in the (X,Y,Z) coordinate system, where X is the major radius axis for phi = 0, Y is the major radius axis for phi = pi/2, and Z is the height axis. The X1 vector is more horizontal than X2 (has a smaller abs(Z) component) and oriented in the positive phi direction (counter-clockwise when viewing from above).

ece.polarizer[:].x1_unit_vector.x_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "x"

ece.polarizer[:].x1_unit_vector.y_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "y"

ece.polarizer[:].x1_unit_vector.z_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"

ece.polarizer[:].x2_unit_vector.documentation: Components of the X2 direction unit vector in the (X,Y,Z) coordinate system, where X is the major radius axis for phi = 0, Y is the major radius axis for phi = pi/2, and Z is the height axis. The X2 axis is orthonormal so that uX2 = uX3 x uX1.

ece.polarizer[:].x2_unit_vector.x_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "x"

ece.polarizer[:].x2_unit_vector.y_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "y"

ece.polarizer[:].x2_unit_vector.z_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"

ece.polarizer[:].x3_unit_vector.documentation: Components of the X3 direction unit vector in the (X,Y,Z) coordinate system, where X is the major radius axis for phi = 0, Y is the major radius axis for phi = pi/2, and Z is the height axis. The X3 axis is normal to the polarizer plane and oriented towards the plasma.

ece.polarizer[:].x3_unit_vector.x_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "x"

ece.polarizer[:].x3_unit_vector.y_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "y"

ece.polarizer[:].x3_unit_vector.z_error_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z"
